        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 26 at 3:50PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ballentine, or near Irmo, moving northeast at 20 mph.

...Boaters on Lake Murray Should Seek Safe Harbor...

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbia, Irmo, St. Andrews, Ballentine, Columbia International
University, Killian, Harbison State Forest, Blythewood, Lighthouse
Marina, Lake Murray Marina, White Rock, Upper Richland Fire Station,
and Cedar Creek Fire Station.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 26 between mile markers 93 and 103.
Interstate 77 between mile markers 20 and 31.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
